  "text": "The Kafka consumer group rebalance protocol implementation in Apache Kafka includes 11 Java source files with 'Rebalance' in their class names located in the clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ directory and its subdirectories.\n\n### Callback Handlers\nThe rebalance protocol uses callback handlers to notify applications of partition assignment changes:\n1. **ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker** - Invokes ConsumerRebalanceListener callback methods (onPartitionsAssigned, onPartitionsRevoked, onPartitionsLost) when consumer group partition assignments change\n2. **ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName** - Enum providing type-safe references to ConsumerRebalanceListener interface method names for compile-time assurance\n3. **StreamsRebalanceListener** - Interface defining callbacks for Kafka Streams when stream task assignments change (onTasksRevoked, onTasksAssigned, onAllTasksLost)\n4. **StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker** - Invokes StreamsRebalanceListener callback methods when stream task assignments change in the Streams rebalance protocol\n\n### Data Structures\n1. **StreamsRebalanceData** - Central data holder for Kafka Streams rebalance protocol participation, containing nested classes:\n   - TaskId: Identifies individual stream tasks\n   - Assignment: Represents active, standby, and warmup task assignments\n   - Subtopology: Defines stream topology information\n   - TopicInfo: Metadata about topics (partitions, replication factor, configs)\n   - HostInfo: Stream instance endpoint information\n   - EndpointPartitions: Maps partitions to endpoint hosts\n\n### Metrics Managers\nThe rebalance protocol tracks metrics through a hierarchy of metrics managers:\n1. **RebalanceMetricsManager** (abstract) - Base class defining the interface for rebalance metrics tracking with methods for recording rebalance start/end events\n2. **RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager** - Tracks latency metrics for rebalance listener callback execution (partition revoke/assign/lost latencies)\n3. **ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager** - Extends RebalanceMetricsManager to track comprehensive consumer group rebalance metrics including latency (avg/max), total rebalance count, rate per hour, and failed rebalance tracking\n4. **ShareRebalanceMetricsManager** - Extends RebalanceMetricsManager to track share consumer group rebalance metrics including total count and rate per hour\n\n### Events\nThe rebalance protocol uses events to coordinate between the I/O thread and application thread:\n1. **ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent** - Signal from I/O thread requesting the application thread invoke a specific rebalance listener callback with given partitions\n2. **ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent** - Signal from application thread indicating a rebalance listener callback has been executed, including any errors that occurred\n\nThese components work together in the rebalance protocol: The coordinator initiates rebalance through events, metrics managers track the process, callback invokers execute user-defined logic at appropriate times, and data structures maintain rebalance state and assignments."
}

