tion revoke/assign/lost latencies)\n3. **ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager** - Extends RebalanceMetricsManager to track comprehensive consumer group rebalance metrics including latency (avg/max), total rebalance count, rate per hour, and failed rebalance tracking\n4. **ShareRebalanceMetricsManager** - Extends RebalanceMetricsManager to track share consumer group rebalance metrics including total count and rate per hour\n\n### Events\nThe rebalance protocol uses events to coordinate between the I/O thread and application thread:\n1. **ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent** - Signal from I/O thread requesting the application thread invoke a specific rebalance listener callback with given partitions\n2. **ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent** - Signal from application thread indicating a rebalance listener callback has been executed, including any errors that occurred\n\nThese components work together in the rebalance protocol: The coordinator initiates rebalance through events, metrics managers track the process, callback invokers execute user-defined logic at appropriate times, and data structures maintain rebalance state and assignments."
